[3
Date: 28 Oct 2001
From: ProMEDmail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AP Online 27 Oct 2001 12:29 p.m. EDT [edited
<http://www.nandotimes.com/nation/story/158730p-1502368c.html>

Washington DC
-------------------
Anthrax spores still being found in Congress
-------------------------------------------------------
Anthrax spores have now turned up at a total of 11 locations on
Capitol Hill. Tests confirmed Friday that anthrax spores were in the
offices of Reps. John E. Baldacci, D-Maine; Rush Holt, D-N.J., and
Mike Pence, R-Ind., on the sixth and seventh floors of the Longworth
House Office Building, said Capitol Police Lt. Dan Nichols.
On Saturday Dr. Gregory Martin reported that the new findings were
low-levels of contamination. Martin, chief of the infectious diseases
service at the National Naval Medical Center, said that for safety's
sake staffers in the three offices are being provided with an
antibiotic.
Pence said his staff is going through visitor records to contact
anyone who had been in his office since 11 Oct 2001 to advise them to
go to their doctor for antibiotics.
Senators and representatives could not get their mail, which was
halted as a precaution the day the potentially deadly letter arrived
in Daschle's office. Their mail continues to pile up and it is unclear
when it will resume. With no one absolutely certain whether other
anthrax-laden letters are still out there, there has been talk of
burning some of the mail. Daschle said he normally receives 5000 to
6000 letters weekly, and Sen. Dianne Feinstein, D-Calif., normally
gets 20 000 letters a week, said her spokesman, Howard Gantman.
(By Alan Fram, Associated Press)
[Some bragging is going on here. - Mod.MHJ
